#)What is a Subpackage in Java? 
A subpackage is a package inside another package.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
com
 └── company
      └── service
            └── impl
Here:

com.company → main package
com.company.service → subpackage 
com.company.service.impl → subpackage inside a subpackage

---------------------------------------------------------------
#)How to Define a Subpackage
package com.company.service.impl;

🔍 Important Interview Point
Subpackages do NOT inherit classes from parent packages.
You must explicitly import them.

Example:
import com.company.service.UserService


