#)What are the types of packages in Java?

There are two types:
--------------------------------------------------------
1. Built-in packages (Java API)

Examples:

java.lang
java.util
java.io
java.net

2. User-defined packages

Created by developers:
package com.myapp.controller;


----------------------------------------------------------------
#)How do you create a user-defined package?
package com.app.model;

public class User {}
The package statement must be the first line in the file.

----------------------------------------------------------
How do you import a package in Java?
import com.app.model.User;
--------------------------------------------------------
Can we access a class without importing the package?

👉 Yes, using fully qualified name.

com.app.model.User user = new com.app.model.User();
-------------------------------------------------------------
#)What happens if two classes have the same name in different packages?

Two classes with the same name Student
1. Class in package school
package school;

public class Student {
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("Student from School");
    }
}
---------------------------------------------

2. Class in package college
package college;

public class Student {
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("Student from College");
    }
}

🎉 Now using both in the same Java file
import school.Student;  // import FIRST Student

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Student s1 = new Student();  
        s1.show();   // prints: Student from School

        // For SECOND Student, use fully qualified name
        college.Student s2 = new college.Student();
        s2.show();   // prints: Student from College
    }
}
